  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease is the major cause of morbidity and mortality in
      Western societies. It is a complex genetic disorder with many genes involved and significant
      gene-environment interactions. The aim of the study is to identify novel genetic- and
      biological-markers of atherosclerosis. Atherosclerosis is assessed in the coronary arteries
      using coronary angiography as well as in the carotid artery (intima-media-thickness) and
      peripheral vessels (ankle brachial index). Association analysis of genetic and metabolic
      markers with atherosclerotic burden will be performed to identify novel factors of
      disposition to atherosclerotic vascular disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
